title: sql_multi_filter
code:
import privpy as pp
import sys
import os
sys.path.append(os.getcwd() + '/privpy_lib')
import pnumpy as pnp
import psql as psq
table = pnp.reshape(pp.ss("gold"), (1940,4))
colm10,colm11,colm12,colm13,= table.trans()
del table
conj0 = (colm13==5152)
conj1 = (colm12<=3948)
conj2 = (colm12>=3946)
conj3 = ( 1 - (1 - (colm10<20181031)) * (1 - ((colm10==20181031)*(colm11<=95838463))))
conj4 = ( 1 - (1 - (colm10>20181031)) * (1 - ((colm10==20181031)*(colm11>=95327897))))
conjs0 =conj0*conj1*conj2*conj3*conj4
del conj0
del conj1
del conj2
del conj3
del conj4
colm12 = psq.count(colm12, condition = conjs0)

colm12 = pp.farr([colm12])
colm12 = colm12.trans()
pp.reveal(colm12, "a3")
